This paper is primarily focused on the problem of learning neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of stochastic gradient descent (SGD) for optimization, which is a common technique in neural network training and falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the application of neural networks for multi-class classification, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the analysis of empirical studies on synthetic data and the MNIST dataset, which falls under the category of data science (cs.DS).
